    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>So, if Don Imus says ''nappy-headed ho,'' he's a pariah, and should be pilloried. Your friend responds to a question from a stranger that can only remotely be considered race related, and responds with the same epithet against an uninvolved person, and, coming from him as a black person, it is heralded as brilliant repartee against the scourge of racism, or at least social oafishness.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>So, if Don Imus says ''nappy-headed ho,'' he's a pariah, and should be pilloried. Your friend responds to a question from a stranger that can only remotely be considered race related, and responds with the same epithet against an uninvolved person, and, coming from him as a black person, it is heralded as brilliant repartee against the scourge of racism, or at least social oafishness.</p>
        <p>Double standard, anyone? I would suggest that the phrase is inappropriate for both Don Imus and your friend.</p>
        <p>Gus Baldini  Binghamton, N.Y.</p>
      </block>
